message.content: We are given that $\frac{1}{p} + \frac{1}{q} = 1$. Clearing the denominators gives $q + p = pq$. Since $pq = 4$, it follows that $q + p = 4$. Since $p >1$ and $q >1$, the only pair of $p$ and $q$ that satisfy this equation is $p=3$ and $q=1$. However, $q>1$, so there are no values of $p$ and $q$ that satisfy the given conditions. Thus, there is no value of $q$, so the answer is $\boxed{\text{no solution}}$.
